{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-srd-template-js","path":"/srd/recruiting-help/","result":{"data":{"page":{"html":"<h1 id=\"recruiting-help\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#recruiting-help\" aria-label=\"recruiting help permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Recruiting help</h1>\n<p>A pair of helping paws might give you the edge you’ll need to survive. Throughout the mouse kingdoms you’ll come across other mice who are willing to explore the vast unknown world with you and your party.</p>\n<h2 id=\"hirelings\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#hirelings\" aria-label=\"hirelings permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Hirelings</h2>\n<p>In a mouse settlement, you can spend a day asking around for mice looking for work. The size of the settlement determines what types of hireling are available. Smaller settlements may not have skilled mice looking for work.</p>\n<h3 id=\"recruiting-hirelings\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#recruiting-hirelings\" aria-label=\"recruiting hirelings permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Recruiting hirelings</h3>\n<p>Make a <strong>WIL save</strong> or <strong>pay</strong> 20p. If successful (or 20p is paid), roll the <strong>Number</strong> for the type of hireling you are interested in employing to determine how many are looking for work.</p>\n<p>Typical hirelings will have:<br>\nd6 hp, STR 2d6, DEX 2d6, WIL 2d6</p>\n<p>Hirelings have 6 inventory slots: two paw, two body, two pack.</p>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Hireling</th>\n<th>Number</th>\n<th>Wages/day</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Torchbearer</td>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>1p</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Labourer</td>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>2p</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Tunnel digger</td>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>5p</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Armourer/blacksmith</td>\n<td>d2</td>\n<td>8p</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Local guide</td>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>10p</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Mouse-at-arms</td>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>10p</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Scholar</td>\n<td>d2</td>\n<td>20p</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Knight</td>\n<td>d3</td>\n<td>25p</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Interpreter</td>\n<td>d2</td>\n<td>30p</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h3 id=\"hireling-morale\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#hireling-morale\" aria-label=\"hireling morale permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Hireling morale</h3>\n<p>When a hireling or warband is placed in a <strong>stressful situation</strong>, made to go without pay or food, or asked to do something more <strong>dangerous</strong> than what they signed on for, they must make a <strong>WIL save</strong> or <strong>flee</strong>.</p>\n<p>Especially well-paid or loyal hirelings may make this save with Advantage.</p>\n<h3 id=\"hireling-advancement\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#hireling-advancement\" aria-label=\"hireling advancement permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Hireling advancement</h3>\n<p>Hirelings and warbands can improve in the same way that your player mice do.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Hirelings who receive a share of treasure gain 1 XP per pip they are given above their daily wage.</li>\n<li>Warbands who receive share of treasure will gain 1 XP per 10 pips they are given above their weekly wage.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Hirelings and warbands advance at the same rate as player mice, so once they get 1000 XP, they advance to Level 2.</p>\n<p>Not receiving a share of treasure may cause resentment amongst hirelings.</p>\n<h2 id=\"warbands\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#warbands\" aria-label=\"warbands permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Warbands</h2>\n<p>A mouse is very small, and many beasts cannot be defeated working alone. When mice work together, they can form a warband, and act on a scale capable of facing other warbands or large beasts, like a cat or boar.</p>\n<h3 id=\"forming-a-warband\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#forming-a-warband\" aria-label=\"forming a warband permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Forming a warband</h3>\n<p>A warband is formed by 20 or more fighting mice, plus one follower (luggage porter, cook, armourer) for every fighter.</p>\n<p>Your mouse can form a warband under their command. In a town or city, spend a week recruiting. Make a WIL save or pay 1000p.</p>\n<p>Warbands start with:<br>\nd6 hp, STR 10, DEX 10, WIL 10<br>\nDamage: d6 clubs and axes</p>\n<p>Warbands require 1000p a week for upkeep and wages. Failure to pay may result in mutiny.</p>\n<h3 id=\"battles\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#battles\" aria-label=\"battles permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Battles</h3>\n<p>Battles between warbands and warband-scale creatures function the same as fights between small individuals. Attacks deal damage to HP, then to STR.</p>\n<p>Attacks by a warband against a non-warband scale creature are enhanced, any damage taken from non-warband scale creatures is ignored unless it is particularly destructive or large scale.</p>\n<h3 id=\"casualties\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#casualties\" aria-label=\"casualties permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Casualties</h3>\n<p>When a warband takes critical damage, they are broken and cannot act until rallied. At STR 0 the warband is wiped out. At half STR, the warband must make a WIL save or be routed.</p>\n<p>Warbands recover HP and attribute score damage like individuals do, with Short, Long and Full rests.</p>\n<h3 id=\"equipping\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#equipping\" aria-label=\"equipping permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Equipping</h3>\n<p>Equipment improves a warband’s abilities the same way as it does for individuals. Just multiply the purchase price by 20.</p>\n<h2 id=\"constructions\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#constructions\" aria-label=\"constructions permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Constructions</h2>\n<p>The <strong>right to build</strong> on land cannot be bought. It can only be given, or taken and defended.</p>\n<p>A team of three tunnel diggers can excavate one 6\" cube of soil per day. Other materials take twice as long.</p>\n<p>Rooms can be of any size — the following is the cost of materials and fittings per 6\" cube constructed. Labourers and diggers must be paid separately.</p>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Room</th>\n<th>Cost</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Tunnel, per 6\"</td>\n<td>10p</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Poor room, per 6\" cube</td>\n<td>100p</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Standard room, per 6\" cube</td>\n<td>500p</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Grand room, per 6\" cube</td>\n<td>2000p</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>All constructions require an <strong>upkeep</strong> of 1% of the total cost per month.</p>","frontmatter":{"slug":"recruiting-help","title":"Recruiting help"}},"toc":{"edges":[{"node":{"markdown":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Brave mice in a dangerous world","section":"Player rules","slug":"brave-mice-dangerous-world"}}}},{"node":{"markdown":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Make a mouse","section":"Player rules","slug":"make-a-mouse"}}}},{"node":{"markdown":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Inventory","section":"Player rules","slug":"inventory"}}}},{"node":{"markdown":{"frontmatter":{"title":"How to play","section":"Player rules","slug":"how-to-play"}}}},{"node":{"markdown":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Magic","section":"Player rules","slug":"magic"}}}},{"node":{"markdown":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Recruiting help","section":"Player rules","slug":"recruiting-help"}}}},{"node":{"markdown":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Running Mausritter","section":"GM rules and resources","slug":"running-mausritter"}}}},{"node":{"markdown":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Creatures","section":"GM rules and resources","slug":"creatures"}}}},{"node":{"markdown":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Hexcrawl toolbox","section":"GM rules and resources","slug":"hexcrawl-toolbox"}}}},{"node":{"markdown":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Adventure site toolbox","section":"GM rules and resources","slug":"adventure-site-toolbox"}}}},{"node":{"markdown":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Useful tables","section":"GM rules and resources","slug":"useful-tables"}}}}]}},"pageContext":{"title":"Recruiting help","section":"Player rules","slug":"recruiting-help"}},"staticQueryHashes":["3449107851"],"slicesMap":{}}